Docs.param: The callback interface to be added to the list. Must not be null -- passing null here will cause a NullPointerException. Most services will want to check for null before calling this with an object given from a client, so that clients can't crash the service with bad data.
Optional additional data to be associated with this callback.
Docs.summary: Add a new callback to the list.
Docs.returns: Returns true if the callback was successfully added to the list. Returns false if it was not added, either because #kill had previously been called or the callback's process has gone away.
